# Rule 04: Rule Precedence and Meta-Governance

## Rule Precedence Order (highest to lowest)

1. `02-security.md` — Security constraints always win
2. `01-position.md` — Project context always applies
3. `03-style.md` — Style applied to source files
4. `04-meta.md` (this file) — Blueprint governance

## Conflict Resolution

When two rules conflict:
1. Higher precedence rule wins
2. If same precedence: narrower scope wins
3. If scope overlap detected: run `bp verify --level logical` to resolve

## Blueprint Maintenance

- Run `bp verify` before every PR merge
- Run `bp sync` when project structure changes significantly
- Never manually edit `<!-- bp-generated:begin ... -->` blocks — re-run `bp init --force` instead
- Add team customizations in `<!-- bp:preserve -->` blocks

